cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of binary networks for image classification tasks on CIFAR-100 and ImageNet datasets. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a methodology for designing mixed-precision networks using Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and evaluates the performance of the proposed Hybrid-Net on various architectures. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper addresses the growing demand for AI-based edge computing and proposes a solution to reduce the computational cost of such applications. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper discusses the use of highly compressed neural networks for energy-efficient neural computing in edge devices. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the energy efficiency of neural networks and proposes a solution to reduce the computational cost of edge devices, which could be of interest to researchers working on hardware architecture for edge devices.
